The Ultimate Ladakh Group Expedition — 16 to 26 June 🚙🏔️

Ladakh is not just a trip, it’s a dream every traveler carries in their heart ♥️And now it’s your chance to live that dream — the real way!

Hi, I’m Ishansh Gupta, and with the amazing team at GCI Adventures, we’re bringing you a once-in-a-lifetime group expedition to Ladakh.

Join our 10-day Ladakh group expedition with 15 SUVs, 30 strangers, and endless memories.

The journey begins from Manali, we’ll pass through the mystical Zanskar Valley, witness the mighty God of Mountains, and explore Padum – the capital of Zanskar.

Then we head to Leh, where the real magic begins…

📍We’ll conquer Umling La Pass — the world’s highest motorable road
📍Stay overnight in Hanle – the darkest village of India for unreal stargazing ✨
📍And finally, witness the divine beauty of Pangong Lake – one of the most breathtaking sights on Earth

So, if Ladakh is on your bucket list this year, comment “LADAKH” and we’ll send you the full itinerary and details.

Bali’s Temple Run Quad Bike Adventure Begins! 🏍🌴

If you’re in Bali and don’t do the Temple Run quad bike ride — did you even come to Bali? 👀

Here’s how I prepped for this epic ride! 💥

👁 First — Contact Lenses
Because let’s be honest, wearing specs during an adventure? Nope.

📱 Second — Waterproof Pouch
Trust me, with all the water crossings and muddy trails, you’ll want your phone & wallet protected.

👕 Third — Dry-fit & Comfortable Clothes
You’ll be riding through waterfalls, dirt trails, and jungle paths — So wear something light, quick-dry, and adventure-ready.

So… what are we waiting for?
Let’s start the most thrilling ride in Bali — the Temple Run! 🚀 See you on the trail!

Planning a Ladakh Trip? Don’t Miss This 🔥

Ladakh season is ON! And if you’re a biker, now’s the best time to ride to the mountains 🏔️but before you head out, here are 3 non-negotiable things you need to keep in mind 🚨 

1. Safety Gear is a MUST
Carry a certified helmet, riding jacket, and pants that are CE Level 2 approved Ladakh terrain is no joke — don’t underestimate it.

2. Extreme Weather Clothing
When I was crossing Khardung La Pass, it suddenly started snowing ❄️ The cold was intense. If I didn’t have proper thermal gear, riding would’ve been impossible.

3. Always Carry Cash
In remote areas like Pangong Lake and Hanle, there’s no mobile network and no online payments

🔥 Bonus Tip:
Always start your rides early in the morning. In Ladakh, roads that are beautiful by day can become dangerous after dark.
